sec.p:
The method is based on identifying outliers in the distribution of pairwise distances between newly infected cities and the set of infectious cities at the previous time step. Let C be the set of locations in the network. At time tj, we can divide C into the set of infectious locations (that can transmit infection) Itj, and the set of susceptible locations Stj (that can become infected; the risk-set):




Itj={k:tk<tj}







Stj={k:tk≥tj}
